For example, when Marc/Steven dies, the way they explore their inner world is super cool. I liked that they made Harrow this weird psychologist in his head. The way they explored memories and Marc’s trauma was also really interesting
So aside from how much I loved the acting, I thought the story was a lot of fun too. I really liked how this took more risks in story telling in comparison to other marvel franchises

I also loved the journey that Marc/Steven go through over the series and seeing them reconcile by the end. Going into the show, I was really worried that this would just end up with the two bickering the whole time and then begrudgingly agreeing to work together.

I also am glad they didn’t rely heavily on other Marvel franchises and let this be a solid standalone series. It really allowed for these characters to thrive in their own and (hopefully) get new viewers interested in the MCU

Consequently though, I have no clue how they’re going to fit this into the rest of the greater MCU. Which I feel is both good and bad—I just hope whatever they do with moon knight going forward they don’t just shoehorn him in randomly
